mediaNotes: Sounds made by the Black Vulture pictured with blue sky behind him.  In the recording, it is almost a hissing sound.  Maybe a juvenile bird. European Starlings, traffic, me stepping on leaves, crickets and a plane are in the background.

location.name: Lagunas de Oxidación de Jesús de Otoro

mediaNotes: Emergency Call - Wing Beats

I stitched together six consecutive clips, each of which was 55 seconds long. Why the Moth didn't record the extra five seconds is unclear to me. As per eBird policy, I left a 2 second gap between clips; in reality, this was a five second gap. The sound was not normalized to -3db as there didn't seem to be an appreciable difference in quality or loudness after doing so. 

Only the adult is clearly heard in this recording, as far as I can tell. A whinny is heard at 2:00, perhaps of a BCCH. A Gray Catbird or squirrel is heard at 1:40. AMGO at 2:20 and 4:45. A fly at 3:18 and later.
